    "body": "@anastasiyaig I found that we're not able to close the app if you just start it and don't log in into it (most likely @iurimatias meant on that case :) ) cause in any other case, as you recorded we're able to close it. \n\nHow it works now on macOs:\n\n- A user is not logged in:\n\n| Action  | \"Minimize on close\" set to true | \"Minimize on close\" set to false |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| close on \"X\" button | minimize | close |\n| close on \"Quit\" from the dock | close | close |\n| close on \"Quit\" | close | close |\n| close on \"Quit Status\" from the app menu bar | close | close |\n\n- A user is logged in:\n\n| Action  | \"Minimize on close\" set to true | \"Minimize on close\" set to false |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| close on \"X\" button | minimize | close |\n| close on \"Quit\" from the dock | close | close |\n| close on \"Quit\" | close | close |\n| close on \"Quit Status\" from the app menu bar | close | close |\n| close on Profile > \"Sign out & Quit\" | close | close |",
